mag\nand E(B-V) = 0.038+/-0.053 mag. The period-age relations are used to derive the\nage of the Cepheid populations in the LMC and SMC. We investigate age and\nspatio-temporal distributions of Cepheids to understand the recent star\nformation history in the Magellanic Clouds (MCs) and found an evidence of a\ncommon enhanced Cepheid population in the MCs at around 200 Myr ago which\nappears to have occurred due to close encounter between the two clouds.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 11 Jun 2019 10:13:38 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 18 Jun 2019 11:43:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-07"}
{"id":"1906.04482","submitter":"Ram  Kishor","authors":"Ram Kishor, M. Xavier James Raj, Bhola Ishwar","title":"Normalization of Hamiltonian and nonlinear stability of triangular\n  equilibrium points in the photogravitational restricted three body problem\n  with P-R drag in non-resonance case","comments":"21 Pages","journal-ref":"Qualitative Theory of Dynamical Systems (Springer Nature), 2019","doi":"10.1007/s12346-019-00327-7","report-no":null,"categories":"nlin.CD astro-ph.EP","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Normal forms of Hamiltonian are very important to analyze the nonlinear\nstability of a dynamical system in the vicinity of invariant objects. This\npaper presents the normalization of Hamiltonian and the analysis of nonlinear\nstability of triangular equilibrium points in non-resonance case, in the\nphotogravitational restricted three body problem under the influence of\nradiation pressures and P-R drags of the radiating primaries. The Hamiltonian\nof the system is normalized up to fourth order through Lie transform method and\nthen to apply the Arnold-Moser theorem, Birkhoff normal form of the Hamiltonian\nis computed followed by nonlinear stability of the equilibrium points is\nexamined. Similar to the case of classical problem, we have found that in the\npresence of assumed perturbations, there always exists one value of mass\nparameter within the stability range at which the discriminant $D_4$ vanish,\nconsequently, Arnold-Moser theorem fails, which infer that triangular\nequilibrium points are unstable in nonlinear sense within the stability range.\nPresent analysis is limited up to linear effect of the perturbations, which\nwill be helpful to study the more generalized problem.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 11 Jun 2019 10:15:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-06-12"}
